    "description": "The CFD model shall demonstrate performance consistent with industry standard practice for blood-contacting device simulation, producing hemolysis predictions that have minimal impact on the regulatory conclusion and show reasonable agreement with available experimental reference data. The model shall adequately capture the relevant flow physics under conditions representative of the intended clinical use.",
    "acceptanceCriteria": "Model outputs shall be within an acceptable range of experimental measurements, as determined by standard engineering judgment applied to hemolysis-sensitive flow metrics. Predictions that are broadly consistent with published reference values and do not materially affect the comparative hemolysis assessment shall be considered satisfactory."
